### INSTRUCTIONS ###

1) Move the CLAUDE-CODE directory into the USER Module directory.

2) Move the included 15_CLAUDE-CODE.sh script into the USER Module directory.
	- Up one level from the CLAUDE-CODE directory

3) On first boot after enabling this module:
	- Open a terminal and run `claude` to start Claude Code
	- Use the `/login` command to authenticate with your Claude account
	- Your configuration is automatically saved to persistent storage

Notes:
- This module requires an active internet connection during Station Setup.

- Configuration is automatically persistent - you only need to log in once.
  Your credentials are stored in /arcHIVE/QRV/$MYCALL/SAVED/CLAUDE-CODE/

- The "Save Claude Code Config" desktop launcher can verify your config is persistent.

- The module will be active on the next reboot or re-run of Station Setup.

- To deactivate the module, place the 15_CLAUDE-CODE.sh script back inside the
  CLAUDE-CODE directory and reboot.

### USAGE ###

After installation, use Claude Code from any terminal:

	claude "your coding task here"

Note: The command is 'claude', not 'claude-code'.
